President Trump and Chancellor Merkel recently had a phone conversation where they discussed various topics including NATO, the Middle East and North Africa, relations with Russia, and the Ukraine crisis. They both emphasized the importance of close German-American cooperation for the security and prosperity of their countries and expressed a desire to strengthen their relations in the future. They also recognized the significance of NATO in maintaining peace and stability in the North Atlantic community and agreed that it should be capable of addressing 21st-century threats. Additionally, they agreed to enhance cooperation in combating terrorism and stabilizing conflict areas in the Middle East and North Africa. President Trump accepted Chancellor Merkel's invitation to attend the G-20 Summit in Germany in July and expressed his anticipation of hosting her in Washington soon.